      "writtenOn": "2017-06-15T20:09:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "“Checked” makes it sound like there’s a CHECK() going on (particularly in Crashpad in light of functions like CheckedReadFileExactly()). Probably just “GetRegisterSet” is enough, and the fact that it indicates success in its return value is normal enough in our code that it doesn’t need to be called out in the function’s name.",
      "revId": "e61b194fa50ab0cf997b8f31b35f460398ce056b",
