        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-15T20:09:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If you do\n\n  template \u003ctypename Destination\u003e\n  bool CheckedGetRegisterSet(pid_t tid, int set, Destination* dest)\n\nthen you don’t need to accept a “size” parameter, you can write sizeof(*dest) instead. That’s nice, it makes things a little less error-prone.\n\nYou can even omit “int set” by deducing it from the Destination type if you want via a traits class.",
      "revId": "e61b194fa50ab0cf997b8f31b35f460398ce056b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
