      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-15T20:09:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suppose that an x86 that doesn’t support fxsave (original SSE) is so ancient that we don’t need to worry about supporting it here.\n\nIn the future, when we add support for further extensions like AVX and AVX-512, we will need to be mindful of the fact that not all systems will have support, and we’ll need to start indicating which register sets we were able to collect. But we can cross that bridge (for all operating systems) when we reach it.",
      "revId": "e61b194fa50ab0cf997b8f31b35f460398ce056b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
